[2] Liquid End Version 
    NP - Clear acrylic with Teflon diaphragm
[3] Gasket
    B - FPM seals
[4] $ - Dosing Head Version
    0 - No bleed valve, no valve springs
    2 - With bleed valve, no valve springs
[5] x  = Controls.
    Any codes not specifically indicated in the trade name or listing notes represent
    features that do not affect the parts of the pump in contact with the media. Any
    value(x) are acceptable for these codes.
[6] These pumps are approved for use with the following media at the maximum concentrations
    listed below. These products are evaluated by diluting the exposed water treatment
    chemical to its maximum use level (MUL), as defined in NSF/ANSI Standard 50:
    Hydrochloric acid (32.0%) and Sodium hypochlorite (15%).
